{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "648b5a6f417cc3fb48d6806e", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eba2"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "63f499841d196b49d9cd6b0b", "title": "JEE Main 2023 (25 Jan Shift 1)", "isVisible": true}], "position": 0, "type": "numerical", "level": 2, "approximateTimeRequired": 180, "question": {"text": "A ray of light is incident from air on a glass plate having thickness <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math> and refractive index <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></math>. The angle of incidence of a ray is equal to the critical angle for glass-air interface. The lateral displacement of the ray when it passes through the plate is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>_</mi><mi>_</mi><mi>_</mi><mi>_</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><msup><mn>10</mn><mo>-</mo></msup><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>cm</mi></math> . (given <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>26</mn></math>)", "image": null}, "options": [], "correctValue": "52", "solution": {"text": "<p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/681a207b-9ffa-48f1-84b2-db7a7f58c5bd-9894213.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 289px;\" /></p><p>Let&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi></math>&nbsp;be the critical angle.</p><p>Then,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sinC</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>&#956;</mi></mfrac></math>,&nbsp;where, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#956;</mi></math> is the refractive index of glass.</p><p>So,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sinC</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mo>&#8658;</mo></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>45</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math></p><p>As the angle of incidence is equal to the critical angle, so using Snell&#39;s law,</p><p>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sinC</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>sin</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo></msqrt><mi>sin</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math></p><p>Now, lateral displacement of the ray is&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>i</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>sec</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>r</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mi>sin</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>45</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></mrow></mfenced><mi>sec</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>26</mn><mo>)</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mfrac></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>52</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>52</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow